# Primer — Functional Color Tokens

Sourced from `primer/primitives` `src/tokens/functional/color/`. Values shown are the light theme defaults; dark theme overrides are noted where they differ significantly.

Token names correspond to CSS variables: `fgColor-default` → `var(--fgColor-default)`.

---

## Foreground (`fgColor`)

| Token | Light value | Dark override | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `fgColor-default` | `neutral.13` (near-black) | `neutral.12` | Primary text — headings, body, labels |
| `fgColor-muted` | `neutral.9` (mid-gray) | — | Secondary text — timestamps, metadata, helper text |
| `fgColor-onEmphasis` | `neutral.0` (white) | `neutral.13` | Text on emphasis backgrounds |
| `fgColor-onInverse` | `neutral.0` (white) | — | Text on inverse backgrounds |
| `fgColor-link` | `accent` blue | — | Interactive link text |
| `fgColor-disabled` | — | — | Disabled text and icons |
| `fgColor-accent` | Blue | — | Accent foreground for links and active states |
| `fgColor-success` | Green | — | Success state text and icons |
| `fgColor-attention` | Yellow/amber | — | Warning state text and icons |
| `fgColor-danger` | Red | — | Error/danger text and icons |
| `fgColor-open` | Green | — | Open PR/issue state |
| `fgColor-closed` | Red | — | Closed PR/issue state |
| `fgColor-done` | Purple | — | Completed/merged state |
| `fgColor-sponsors` | Magenta/pink | — | GitHub Sponsors context |

