## Component token patterns

Component tokens follow this naming convention:
`{component}-{property}-{variant}`

Examples:
- `control-borderColor-default` — default border for form controls
- `control-borderColor-danger` — error border for form controls
- `focus-outlineColor` — focus ring color (accent color in all themes)
- `selection-bgColor` — selected text background

---

## Usage notes

- **Never use base tokens directly** (`color-scale-blue-5`). Always use functional or component tokens.
- **`fgColor-onEmphasis` is mandatory** when text appears on any `bgColor-*.emphasis` background.
- **Semantic role tokens** (`fgColor-success`, `bgColor-danger-muted`, etc.) automatically adapt to the active theme — use them instead of hue-specific tokens.
- **Nine themes** share the same token names; values are compiled per theme at build time.
